</div>

<p>Learning short valid words like IT gives you critical flexibility in the endgame. When the bag is empty and both players can see the remaining tiles, having a catalogue of short words means you can always make a legal play — avoiding the penalty of passing or exchanging. Tournament players memorise hundreds of two and three-letter words specifically for these tight endgame situations.</p>

